{"type":"message","id":"a477b02d","parentId":"91e70938","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:10:32.615Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the pulse ran. Now let me read the most recent log file.","thinkingSignature":"666854d695f624a0e976a7ec8ab7934c059dfa71b8f57916822a19d0081b0c61"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_th12mj27ktj5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 040816.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":428,"output":70,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12452,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774339830208}}
{"type":"message","id":"3c0a54ff","parentId":"a477b02d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:10:32.623Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_th12mj27ktj5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 040816\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: scripts/tic_classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a pending TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n3. The next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is key - causal structure IS invariant structure. The next step is to implement the TIC classifier experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the logs directory and see what pulse logs exist.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action I can take right now is to:\r\n1. Look at existing pulse logs to understand their format\r\n2. Start implementing the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nSince I need to be specific and do a file edit, I should:\r\n1. Check what pulse log files exist\r\n2. Create a basic TIC classifier script\r\n\r\nLet me write the TIC experiment implementation. This is the pending next action from the goals.\r\n\r\nI'll create a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features from each pulse\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n4. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 advancement goal directly.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to examine the pulse log format and implement the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that reads pulse logs, extracts structural features, classifies invariant vs variant content, and measures prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\nSuccess criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMETADATA_FILE = Path(\"research/pulse_metadata.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_features(pulse_text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structural features from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    features = {\r\n        'lines': len(pulse_text.split('\\n')),\r\n        'sections': pulse_text.count('##'),\r\n        'bullet_points': pulse_text.count('- '),\r\n        'code_blocks': pulse_text.count('```'),\r\n        'urls': len(re.findall(r'https?://[^\\s]+', pulse_text)),\r\n        'file_refs': len(re.findall(r'[a-zA-Z0-9_/-]+\\.(md|py|ps1|txt)', pulse_text)),\r\n        'has_goals': 'Goals:' in pulse_text or '# Goals' in pulse_text,\r\n        'has_observation': 'OBSERVATION' in pulse_text,\r\n        'has_action': 'ACTION' in pulse_text,\r\n        'has_mutation': 'MUTATION' in pulse_text,\r\n    }\r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(features_prev, features_curr):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify what changed between pulses.\r\n    Invariant = same structure (goals, sections, format)\r\n    Variant = content changes (goals updated, new sections, etc.)\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    invariants = []\r\n    variants = []\r\n    \r\n    # Structural invariants (format should be stable)\r\n    if features_curr['has_goals'] == features_prev.get('has_goals'):\r\n        invariants.append('goals_presence')\r\n    else:\r\n        variants.append('goals_changed')\r\n    \r\n    if features_curr['has_observation'] == features_prev.get('has_observation'):\r\n        invariants.append('observation_presence')\r\n    else:\r\n        variants.append('observation_changed')\r\n    \r\n    # Line count variance indicates content drift\r\n    line_diff = abs(features_curr['lines'] - features_prev.get('lines', 0))\r\n    if line_diff < 5:\r\n        invariants.append('stable_length')\r\n    else:\r\n        variants.append(f'length_drift_{line_diff}')\r\n    \r\n    return invariants, variants\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_from_invariants(pulses_features):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse structure from invariant patterns.\"\"\"\r\n    if len(pulses_features) < 3:\r\n        return None\r\n    \r\n    # Average features from last N pulses to predict next\r\n    recent = pulses_features[-3:]\r\n    predicted = {}\r\n    for key in recent[0].keys():\r\n        values = [p[key] for p in recent]\r\n        if isinstance(values[0], bool):\r\n            predicted[key] = sum(values) / len(values) > 0.5\r\n        else:\r\n            predicted[key] = sum(values) // len(values)\r\n    return predicted\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    # Collect pulse logs\r\n    log_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    if len(log_files) < 5:\r\n        print(f\"Need at least 5 pulse logs, found {len(log_files)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Limit to last 20\r\n    log_files = log_files[-20:]\r\n    print(f\"Analyzing {len(log_files)} pulse logs\")\r\n    \r\n    # Extract features from each pulse\r\n    pulses_features = []\r\n    for log in log_files:\r\n        text = log.read_text()\r\n        features = extract_pulse_features(text)\r\n        pulses_features.append(features)\r\n    \r\n    # Classify invariants vs variants\r\n    invariant_count = 0\r\n    variant_count = 0\r\n    classifications = []\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(1, len(pulses_features)):\r\n        invariants, variants = classify_invariant(pulses_features[i-1], pulses_features[i])\r\n        classifications.append((invariants, variants))\r\n        invariant_count += len(invariants)\r\n        variant_count += len(variants)\r\n    \r\n    total = invariant_count + variant_count\r\n    invariant_ratio = invariant_count / total if total > \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:08:49\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774339832622}}
{"type":"message","id":"86b9d103","parentId":"3c0a54ff","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:10:46.442Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me summarize the pulse results for Zach.","thinkingSignature":"514d3d82ca6e707c4ebcae0afed9a307fdb8cd188631813e2856099856b19985"},{"type":"text","text":"### Sandbox Pulse Summary — Mar 24, 04:10 AM\n\n**What happened:** The pulse ran and focused on the **TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment** — the next logical step in validating the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis.\n\n**Key observations:**\n- Phases 0–1 of the research are complete\n- TIC experiment is pending implementation — the classifier script was being created in this pulse\n- The hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure (structural patterns repeat, content changes)\n- Proposed mutation count: **1** (waiting to be applied)\n\n**Next step flagged:** Implement the TIC classifier on pulse logs to measure:\n- >70% classification accuracy (invariant vs variant)\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy from invariant patterns\n\nNo applied mutations this cycle — the pulse was planning rather than executing. The classifier script appears to have been cut off mid-write in the log."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1809,"output":201,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13964,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774339832623}}
